Shehu Sani, a former Kaduna Central Senator, has condemned the attack on the country home of Ohanaeze Ndigbo President-General, George Obiozor. Sani described the attack on Obiozor’s home as unfortunate. The socio-political activist urged security agencies to ensure that those behind the attack are made to face the wrath of the law. In a tweet, Sani wrote: “The attacks on the country home of the President-General of the Ohanaeze, Professor George Obiozor in Imo State is unfortunate and condemnable. The arsonists must not go scot-free.” Obiozor’s home was razed by unknown assailants. Prof Obiozor’s country home is located in Oru East Local Government Area of Imo State. The arsonists were said to have used Improvised Explosives Devices, IEDs, and petrol bombs to raze down the building. The incident was confirmed by Micheal Abatta, Imo State Police Public Relations Officer.